text.body:
IN THE DISTRICT COURT OF THE THIRD JUDICIAL DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON TERRITORY, HOLDING TERMS AT SEATTLE, KING COUNTY.
In the matter of the application of William W. Tinkham, for a writ of HABEAS ORDER GRANTING WRIT. CORPUS.
On reading and filing the petition of William W. Tinkham, duly signed and verified by him, whereby it appears that he is illegaly imprisoned and restrained of his liberty by Jasper Gates, Deputy Constable of Skagit County, Washington Territory, at the City of Seattle, King County, Washington Territory, and stating wherein the illegality consists, from which it appears to me that a writ of HABEAS CORPUS ought to issue.
It is ordered that a writ of HABEAS CORPUS issue out of and under the seal of the District Court of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory, directed to the said Jasper Gates, commanding him to have the body of the said William W. Tinkham before me, in the Court room of the County of King, Territory of Washington, on the 20 day of September, 1887, at the hour of five o'clock P.M. to do and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning the said William W. Tinkham, together with the time and cause of his detention, and that he have then and there the said writ. And that he be admitted to bail in the sum of ///
Dated on the 10 day of September, 1887
R.A. Jones, Judge
No.5524
In the matter of the application of William W. Tinkham for a writ of Habeas Corpus
Order
FILED Sep 14 1887 W.E. Ledgerwood
BURKE & HALLER, ATTORNEYS-AT-LAW SEATTLE, WASH. TER.
